  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C).",
    " Rinse the cauliflower and break it into florets.",
    "Drizzle the binchotan charcoal pieces with a little bit of oil and roast in the oven for 10 minutes.",
    "Roast the cauliflower in the oven for 15-20 minutes, or until tender.",
    "In a small bowl, mix together the ghee, garlic, lemon juice, chili flakes, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Once the cauliflower is done, toss it with the ghee mixture until well coated.",
    "Transfer the cauliflower to a serving bowl and top with shaved parmesan cheese and fresh parsley.",
    "Drizzle a little bit of oil over the dish and serve immediately."
